AI Analogy

LLMs don’t literally “count steps” through a conversation. They work more like terrain navigation.

They maintain an evolving representation of the conversational landscape and continually re-estimate where they are in that semantic space as new information arrives. If the “terrain” changes, the model can reorient rather than simply extending a previous chain of reasoning.

